The demyelination of the nervous system, which characterizes multiple sclerosis, disrupts the transmission of nerve impulses and affects many body systems; MS impacts joints, muscles, vision, and coordination. It can also lead to depression. MS does not affect cognition.

[$/BLOCK] [$/CELL] [$/BOX]
